A middle aged female patient presented with vesicles and blisters over the skin and oral cavity. On examination, the blisters are flaccid with an erythematous base, and a firm sliding pressure with a finger separates the Superficial epidermis layers from basal epidermis, producing a new lesion. Which of the following microscopic features is not seen in this patient?

 







			{{caption_text}}



			A




			{{caption_text}}



			B






			{{caption_text}}



			C




			{{caption_text}}


			D
